text: My prayers are with the late Rev. Billy Graham’s family and all those whose lives he touched. For decades, his words inspired people around the world. May he rest in peace.

On this Day of Remembrance for Japanese Incarceration, we reflect on the 1942 signing of Executive Order 9066, which led to the detention of over 120,000 Americans based solely on their Japanese ancestry. Let us recommit to fighting for civil liberties & social justice for all.

As we celebrate the #LunarNewYear, let us honor the history, traditions, and rich culture of our Asian American community. I hope all who observe this new year share this joyous time with family and friends. May you enjoy health, happiness, and prosperity in the coming year!

Congrats to the people of South Korea on the opening of the #PyeongChang #WinterOlympics!  I wish #TeamUSA every success at these #Olympics -- and I’m looking forward to the Olympic Flame returning to #LosAngeles for #LA2028 ten short years from now! #OpeningCeremony

I’m deeply disappointed that after this vote, we still don’t have a plan in place to help our #Dreamers. As an original co-author of the #DreamAct, I will keep fighting to #ProtectDreamers so they can pursue their future in our shared homeland of America.

Excited to see #Olympic competitions getting underway today in #PyeongChang. Good luck to America's incredible Olympians -- I know you'll make us proud on the world stage! #USA #WinterOlympics @TeamUSA @Olympics

I was a strong NO vote on tonight's CR, the 5th stopgap spending bill the GOP has brought up this fiscal year. Republicans keep trying to govern by staggering from one manufactured crisis to the next. That's simply wrong. The GOP must work with Democrats to make a long-term deal.
Main takeaway from #AYearOfTrump? The only major bill passed by the GOP is a tax plan that raises taxes on the middle class in order to hand massive tax breaks to corporations and the wealthiest 1%.

Today, on International Holocaust Remembrance Day, we honor the memory of the Holocaust's victims, including the 6 million Jews who perished. Let us unite in saying #NeverAgain, and rededicate ourselves to doing all we can to eradicate genocide.

I opposed today's so-called "deal" on a 3-week continuing resolution. It does not get us any closer to a bipartisan budget agreement that enables us to finish our work on the FY 2018 approps bills, and it does not give us any meaningful certainty about a deal for the #Dreamers.
Democrats are working hard to put an end to the #TrumpShutdown -- just like we tried to keep it from happening in the first place.

The #TrumpShutdown…
-Threatens public health & consumer safety
-Disrupts our economy & job creation
-Blocks services & investments critical to our families & our communities

Republicans control…
-the White House
-the House of Representatives
-the Senate
The #TrumpShutdown is their own doing, and the American people know it.

As the first #MexicanAmerican congresswoman, I was deeply inspired by the crowds who packed the streets at last year’s #WomensMarch. As we celebrate #WomensMarch2018, I continue to stand w/ marchers in resisting the forces of hatred, bigotry, oppression, injustice, & inequality.

Today, as the president begins his second year, I will keep advocating for #ABetterDeal for our communities and our families, so we can build an America that moves forward and leaves no one behind. I urge the president to join us.

I’m sick and tired of watching Republicans treat shutting down government as casually and carelessly as if they were playing with a toy. Their #TrumpShutdown is not going to help ANYONE in my district. I say to the GOP: #DoYourJob!

The LAST thing our country needs is a government shutdown. This #TrumpShutdown won’t help the economy, it won’t help our kids stay healthy, and it won’t help anyone in my district. Frankly, it’s ridiculous that Republicans have brought us to this point. GOP, #DoYourJob!
The government should stay open and working for the American people. The last thing we need is the #TrumpShutdown. Republicans, you need to #DoYourJob!

I opposed tonight's Continuing Resolution because it again delays decisions on the big challenges facing our country -- defense funding, pensions, Dreamers' future, disaster spending, community health centers, and more. We CANNOT keep kicking the can down the road!

REALITY CHECK: The GOP controls both Congress and the White House. They have the votes to keep the govt open. If the govt shuts down, it will be the fault of Republicans who refuse to protect key priorities: Dreamers, children’s health & community health centers. #DoYourJob, GOP!

Today is the anniversary of the 2010 Haiti earthquake. The resilience and resolve that Haitians have shown during the recovery effort continues to inspire the world. To our Haitian brothers and sisters, I say: the American people stand with you.

Happy Thanksgiving to you and your family! May it be a day of cherished company and good food – and let us also take this day to show gratitude for the blessings in our lives.

#StudentLoan debt is out of control in this country. #GOPTaxScam eliminates the student loan interest deduction & makes it harder to repay for the record number of #Latinos enrolling in universities. The end of the tuition deduction will make college unattainable for Latinos.

In 2015, the #ChildTaxCredit kept nearly 1 million #Latinos out of poverty. The #GOPTaxScam would make hard-working families ineligible for this credit, pushing hundreds of thousands of families into poverty.

#GOPTaxScam pays for tax cuts for the richest by making massive spending cuts to key programs that help our 40th District families make ends meet, stay healthy, put food on the table, and keep a roof over their heads.
